ection keys if you can trivially circumvent them?<br /><br />No, we will *not* worry about protection keys in get_user_pages().<br /><br />They are not "security". They are a debug aid and safety against random mis-use.<br /><br />In particular, they are very much *NOT* about "trivially circumvent<br />them". The user could just change their mapping thing, for chrissake!<br /><br />We already allow access to PROT_NONE for gdb and friends, very much on purpose.<br /><br />We're not going to make the VM more complex for something that<br />absolutely nobody cares about, and has zero security issues.<br /><br />                        Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
